Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 2
  Paragraph: 21
Title: Discussion On Making All Things Equal
---
The torch of chaos and doubt - this is what the sage steers by. So he
does not use things but relegates all to the constant. This is what it
means to use clarity.
